                            <comment id="13444909" author="umamaheswararao" created="Thu, 30 Aug 2012 13:25:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a first version of technical doc for this feature.&lt;br/&gt;
Configurations and installations stuff need to update yet.&lt;br/&gt;
Once this is approved here, we can use this content to update in Wiki.&lt;br/&gt;
for SVN commit, will give other patch to commit the datails as documentation. That should cover configurations for Autorecovery process and how to start.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13479217" author="umamaheswararao" created="Thu, 18 Oct 2012 19:30:19 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached an initial patch for the documentaion.&lt;br/&gt;
Also added the info for BK-428, assuming that would provide the same commands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;+If users wanted to disable/enable the this Auto-Recovery service temporarily for some Bookie upgrades or etc, execute the following commands
+ To disable: @bookkeeper-server/bin/bookkeeper autorecovery disable@
+ To enable:  @bookkeeper-server/bin/bookkeeper autorecovery enable@
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
